{
  "stem": "14463.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was something which not only that you sang it because you had to sing it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They sang it because they loved singing it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was a love.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Till today, I've got a love for hazanot, till today.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And so it was intensely, intensely religious, terribly warm hearted, very warm hearted.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they had all sorts of organizations to help.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In my family, my own family, which I remember very well, which will give you some sort of an idea, my grandfather was a very tight man.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was tough, and he was tight.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Grandmother Malka was just the opposite-- soft, wonderful, good hearted, you know?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Not that he wasn't good hearted, but he was good.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Her life was-- what did she do with Chrzanow?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "What was her role in Chrzanow?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Except that she was looking after the children-- she had five children, you know, grandchildren, all that sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She used to give a nadn to a girl which didn't have any parents.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "What does that mean?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A nadn?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She used to give a dowry.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A girl which didn't have-- which was a [NON-ENGLISH]-- you know, she didn't have a mother.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She didn't have a father.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Or she couldn't afford it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So she used to give them a nadn.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She organized a flat where to live.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She had tried to help the young men to get a job, or get into something, so he could make a living.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And what I love most of all, that she made them at the wedding-- the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So the [NON-ENGLISH] was in the synagogue opposite.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And in our place was the reception.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now at the reception-- and grandfather used to-- I'll never ever forget that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then grandfather used to say, make the reception at synagogue.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
